# 6. フィナーレまで共に

Mafuyu: This really is such a large crowd...
Rui: It is one of this season's most famous events. As such, tourists from all over flock to see it, including us.
Airi: Let's see... Based on this flyer...
Airi: The general participants appear first, then people wearing costumes and stuff designed by professionals.
Shizuku: Oh, you can even join on the day by renting a costume...
Tsukasa: Wh-What?! Is that true?!
Mafuyu: Unfortunately, that may be difficult. I just saw a sign towards the entrance that said, “All costumes have been rented out.”
Tsukasa: Ah, darn it...! If only I paid closer attention to what that website said...!
Rui: I feel the same way... We could've all been in it...
Miyake: I-I'm not sure I would've wanted to...
Taniyama: But I kinda wish you guys could be in it, Kamishiro! I bet it'd be great!
Shizuku: I agree. The parade would be guaranteed to be more fun if Tsukasa and Kamishiro were able to participate.
Rui: Hehe. Now I feel even more regretful about not being able to take part...
Tsukasa: But the rules are the rules... So, let's just enjoy it as regular tourists!
Tsukasa: At the same time, that's going to be hard with this many people around. I feel we should move somewhere less crowded...
Airi: Okay! Then... How about over there?
Mafuyu: Try to stay together, everyone.
Shizuku: Then, let's—
Parade Participants: Excuse us! Heavy load coming through!
Nice Old Lady: Oh no...!
Rui: *Gasp* They're going to hit that old lady...!
Shizuku: K-Kamishiro?!
Rui: Are you okay?
Nice Old Lady: ...! Thank you for protecting me...
Rui: No, I'm just glad I could help.
Rui: (But it's not safe here. There's far too many people... We need to find somewhere less crowded to take refuge—)
Rui: (My phone...! I dropped it...!)
Rui: (Oh no, it cracked. But this old lady takes priority right now...)
Shizuku: Are you hurt, Kamishiro?!
Rui: Hinomori...!
Shizuku: Madam, would you like us to help you move somewhere less crowded? If we can get back to the main boulevard...
Nice Old Lady: No, that's okay. My friend should be waiting for me just over there. Thank you very much.
Rui: I see. That's a relief...
Rui: But please be careful. This crowd is making even walking difficult.
Shizuku: *Sigh* Thank goodness she ended up being okay.
Rui: Yes, I'm just as glad. Now, we should get back to...
Shizuku: Wait, where did Airi and the others go...?
Rui: (Did we get separated from them...?)
Rui: We need to contact them and... ...!
Rui: It's no use. The touch screen on my phone's unresponsive after I dropped it.
Shizuku: What...?!
Shizuku: Wh-What should we do...?! My phone has no battery left...
Shizuku: Wait, I know! We can look for a place to charge it! Any convenience store should do...
Rui: Yes, I see... Let's look for one while keeping our ears open for Tsukasa's voice.
Rui: We may just hear him shouting our names somewhere along the way.
Shizuku: Right...!
Tsukasa: Rui!!! Shizuku!!! Where are you two?!?!
Miyake: Kamishiro! Hinomori!
Hayashi & Taniyama: Where are you?!
Airi: Say something if you can hear us!! Huff... Huff... Huff...
Mafuyu: I think our voices are being drowned out by the music and all these other people...
Tsukasa: Huff... Huff... To think that they're unable to hear my booming voice...
Airi: We can't reach Shizuku because her phone has no charge, but I don't understand why we can't get ahold of Kamishiro...
Tsukasa: I don't know either... I hope they weren't swept away somewhere...
Mafuyu: Are they going to be okay...?
Mafuyu: Oh, that sound... I think the parade is about to begin...
Airi: Not good...! Once it starts, more people will gather to watch it! That's only gonna make it harder for us to find them...!
Tsukasa: We need to locate them now.
Tsukasa: Yes, their safety is a top priority...
Tsukasa: But this is also our school trip. Our goal is to watch this parade together.
Tsukasa: So, let's keep looking for them!
Mafuyu & Airi: Yeah! Yes!
Shizuku: Airi! Asahina! Tsukasa!
Shizuku: Airi— *Cough*
Rui: Are you okay?
Shizuku: Yes... It's just my throat...
Rui: Let's stop here. You shouldn't overstrain your voice.
Shizuku: Yes... Still, now that the parade is underway, it seems like there are more people here. What if we can't find the others?
Shizuku: Oh, but... Won't it become easier to find them after it's over?
Rui: After it's over...
Rui: (Yes, she's right...)
Rui: (But...)
Tsukasa: You only get one chance in life as a high schooler to go on this trip! It's like a one-night-only performance!
Miyake: But it would be nice to have you in our group, Kamishiro...!
Rui: Would you mind if we resumed our search?
Shizuku: Huh?
Rui: A school trip... It's akin to a one-night-only performance...
Rui: If possible, I'd like to see the finale as a complete group.
Shizuku: Yes, me too... You're exactly right, Kamishiro.
Shizuku: I'd also like to create as many wonderful memories as I can with everyone. And more importantly...
Shizuku: Airi and the others are very likely still trying their best to find us.
Rui: Yes, you're probably right.
Shizuku: So, should be doing the same!
Rui: Agreed.
Rui: But shouting may not be doing us any good since this crowd seems to be drowning us out...
Rui: If only there were a better way for us to get Tsukasa and the others to notice us...
Tourists: Whoa! That nurikabe looks so real!
Tourists: Same with that nurarihyon... Their makeup looks professionally done.
Rui: Wait, the costumes...
Tourists: Cool! Check out that red ogre! It totally stands out with that giant club!
Rui: It stands out...
Staff Member: Last call for joining the parade with your own costume!
Rui: That's it...!
Rui: Hinomori, I have an idea, but I need your help. Would you mind hearing me out?
Shizuku: What?
